     customInstructions: |
       ## Identity & Code Conventions

       • Use C++17 only, with `std::optional`, `std::variant`, `if constexpr`, and RAII.
       • Header-first development: write `.h` with `#pragma once` before `.cpp`.
       • Prefer `constexpr`, `noexcept`, and smart pointers (`std::unique_ptr`, `std::shared_ptr`).
       • Document all public interfaces with Doxygen `@brief`, `@param`, `@return`, `@throws`.
       • Respect Lorentz signature `(-,+,+,+)` for 4D and `(-,+)` for 2D (dilaton) simulations.
       • Build system: CMake ≥3.16; use `FetchContent` for ImGui, GLFW, glad, stb_image.
       • Testing: Catch2 unit tests in `tests/`; run `ctest` before any merge.

       ## Spacetime & Curvature (4D)

       • Implement `Event4D` (t,x,y,z) with proper time, causal classification, and Lorentz transformations.
       • Provide `MetricTensor` interface; implement `MinkowskiMetric`, `SchwarzschildMetric`, `KerrMetric`, 
         `ReissnerNordstromMetric`, `FRWMetric`.
       • Compute Christoffel symbols, Riemann, Ricci, Ricci scalar, Weyl, and Kretschmann invariants.
       • Support `DifferentiableMetric` with automatic differentiation (forward mode via `ADVariable<N>`).
       • Use `CurvatureCalculator` for numerical finite-difference when symbolic AD is not feasible.

       ## Geodesic Integration

       • Use `GeodesicIntegrator` with adaptive Runge-Kutta (RK4 or Dormand-Prince) for timelike & null geodesics.
       • Tolerance: 1e-8, step range 1e-10 - 0.1, max steps 100k.
       • Provide `DifferentiableGeodesicIntegrator<N>` template for N-parameter gradients.
       • Validate energy conservation (ΔE/E < 1e-6) and convergence order.

       ## 2D Dilaton Gravity (CGHS Model)

       • Implement the CGHS action (Eq. 2.1) with dilaton φ and matter scalar f.
       • Use conformal gauge ds² = -e^{2ρ} dx⁺ dx⁻ with free field ρ-φ.
       • Provide constructors for linear dilaton vacuum (M=0) and black holes (M>0).
       • Support infalling matter f = F(x⁺) to form collapsing black holes.
       • Expose apparent horizon (∂₊φ=0) and singularity at x⁺x⁻ = M.
       • For semiclassical evaporation, add the RST counterterm and solve modified field equations (Eq. 5.22).
       • Track critical line φ_cr (Eq. 5.26) where semiclassical approximation fails.

       ## Hawking Radiation & Quantum Fields

       • Compute renormalised stress tensor ⟨:T_{±±}:⟩_ξ via conformal anomaly.
       • Derive thermal spectrum at T = κ/(2π) using Bogoliubov coefficients.
       • Implement late-time exponential redshift σ⁻ ∝ -e^{-κ ξ⁻}.
       • Validate that asymptotic flux approaches 1/48 (in 2D) or correct Hawking power (4D).
       • For 4D, use `HawkingCalculator` with surface gravity κ = 1/(4M) for Schwarzschild.

       ## Quantum Gravity Engines (Planck-scale)

       • **CDT (Causal Dynamical Triangulations)**: Monte Carlo evolved 4D simplicial manifolds; 
         measure spectral / Hausdorff dimension via `CDTEngine`.
       • **Spin Foam (LQG)**: `SpinNetwork` (SU(2) spins on edges) and `SpinFoamEngine` (EPRL vertex amplitude).
       • **GFT (Group Field Theory)**: `GFTEngine` with tensor networks and condensate solver.
       • **Causal Sets**: Poisson sprinkling, Benincasa-Dowker action, Myrheim-Meyer dimension estimator.
       • For visualisation, use `QuantumGeometryRenderer` with LOD (4 levels) and theory-specific geometry.
       • Integrate with `PlanckMicroscope` for logarithmic zoom from 1 m down to 10⁻³⁵ m.

       ## AI & Differentiable Simulation

       • **Neural ODE surrogate** (`GeodesicNeuralODE`): Python (PyTorch) training → ONNX export → C++ inference.
         Target: <1ms inference, <1% endpoint error, 100× speedup over RK4.
       • **Metric GNN**: predict metric tensor from mass distribution using graph neural networks.
       • **Normalising flow**: unsupervised anomaly detection on curvature patterns (μs inference).
       • **RL discovery agent** (`DiscoveryEngine`): explores theory parameter space with reward = novelty + validity + observational fit.
       • **Differentiable simulator**: end-to-end gradients w.r.t. theory parameters via AD.
       • **Bayesian evidence calculator**: nested sampling for model comparison (GR vs modified theories).
       • **Automated LaTeX paper generator**: collects discoveries into a formatted paper.

       ## Black-Hole Information Paradox

       • Model Hilbert space splitting: outside (O) and hidden (h).
       • Compute entanglement entropy S = -Tr(ρ ln ρ) for outside observer.
       • Simulate interaction Hamiltonian (Eq. 6.15) and test repeatability of information loss.
       • Compare conventional resolutions: loss, return, remnants (Table 1).
       • Use `SingularityHandler` for regular black holes (Hayward, Bardeen, LQG, Gauss) with finite curvature at r=0.

       ## Pair Production & Ernst Instantons

       • Implement Ernst metric (Eq. 7.11) for magnetically charged black holes in Melvin universe.
       • Enforce regularity conditions at both horizons (Eq. 7.17).
       • Compute Euclidean action S_inst = π Q / B and production rate.
       • Explore connection to remnant problem: finite vs infinite states.

       ## Multi-Messenger & Live Data

       • Use `MultiMessengerAdapter` interface; implement `LIGOAdapter` with GraceDB HTTP + VOEvent parsing.
       • Integrate real-time alerts (LIGO, IceCube, CHIME) via WebSocket / GCN.
       • Trigger parameter scans when observational discrepancy >3σ.
       • Provide virtual observatory cross-matcher (SDSS, Gaia) to subtract simulated sky from real images.

       ## Collaborative VR & Metaverse

       • Multi-user server (central authority, 30 Hz broadcast, last-writer-wins).
       • VR clients using OpenXR / WebRTC; each user has `Camera4D` + avatar world-line.
       • Time-locking protocol: users can "park" at a specific proper time and reconvene.
       • Spatial audio: gravitational wave sonification (frequency ∝ curvature).

       ## 4D User Interface (ImGui + GLFW)

       • Extend `UI4D_ImGui` with docking workspace (main 4D view + side panels).
       • Provide linked slice views: fixed-t, proper-time, null, complex (Wick rotated).
       • Add `Camera4D` with 6 rotation planes (tx, ty, tz, xy, xz, yz) and `cyclePlane()` slot.
       • Implement `PlanckMicroscope` panel with logarithmic zoom slider and real-time spectral dimension readout.
       • Provide information dashboard: entropy vs time, entanglement entropy, Hawking flux.
       • Add Pair Production Visualiser (wormhole instanton geometry).

       ## Unit Testing & Scientific Validation

       • Place every feature's test in `tests/` using Catch2.
       • Mandatory validation checks (all must pass):
         - Dilaton vacuum: R=0, φ = -σ
         - Hawking flux: ⟨:T_{±±}:⟩ → 1/48 (2D) at late times
         - Bekenstein-Hawking entropy: S = A/4
         - RST endpoint: horizon-singularity meeting at σ⁻_NS (Eq. 5.26)
         - Pair production action reproduces π Q / B in weak field limit
         - Mercury perihelion precession (43″/century) within 1%
         - Eddington light deflection (1.75″) within 0.5%
         - Gravitational redshift: Δλ/λ = GM/(c²r) exact
         - Frame dragging (Gravity Probe B) 39 mas/year within 0.1 mas
         - Energy conservation ΔE/E < 1e-6 for geodesics over τ=100
         - Differentiable gradients: ∂K/∂M = 96M/r⁶ (error <5%)
       • Reject any result that fails historical tests.
       • Flag curvature anomalies exceeding 5σ (Kretschmann, Ricci, Weyl).

       ## Development Workflow

       1. Write header with clear Doxygen interface first.
       2. Implement functions, commenting physical reasoning (equations from Wald or project docs).
       3. Add unit test (`tests/test_*.cpp`) and update `CMakeLists.txt`.
       4. Run `ctest --output-on-failure` - only proceed if all tests pass.
       5. For new physics, prove concept on a toy model (e.g., 2D dilaton) before scaling to 4D.
       6. For AI components, train in Python (PyTorch), export to ONNX, then integrate C++ inference.
       7. Use the global `Complete Global Integration Plan.md` as the single source of truth.

       ## References (Embedded in Project)

       • `all_info.md` - complete technical reference
       • `Complete Global Integration Plan.md` - master blueprint
       • `README.md` - quick start and file tree
       • `IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md` - architecture and modules
